  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was constant adjusting from one to the other.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was among my first poems, and I would like to share it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'I feel like a bird with clipped wings tied to this earth by invisible strings, chained to a destiny I did not choose.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I feel like a prisoner that cannot break loose.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I look at the sky with a heavy sigh, but my wings have been clipped, and I can no longer fly.' Then I realized that the concept of freedom is a bird in flight and not in a bird in a cage.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I pledged to myself, if I'll get out, I will never use brute force.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I will never try to force somebody to do something, but neither will I allow other people to do it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I understood the concept of freedom.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I understood what my forefathers, what the, the Jews in Egypt, the Israelites in Egypt, must have felt like.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I realized that there is no substitute for personal experience, from knowledge derived from personal experience.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I realized then that nothing in the world, no textbook, no professor, not the best college, could teach me what my experience taught me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because I had to-- I got to know myself, who I am, how much I could endure, how much I could understand, how much I could feel, and what I've became, and saw the world through a completely different things.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I was thinking, Mengele was a university-educated man with doctoral degrees.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had the ability to heal the, the sick, and perversely, he choosed to, to kill the, the healthy imprisoned in Auschwitz, more than 400,000 Jews, [NON-ENGLISH], were murdered because of him, the selections, to the left, to the right.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
